Variation. Color variation occurs in all species, i.e., teneral individuals are pale yellow to light­reddish brown. Morphometrical variation occurs to a remarkable extent in male individuals of all species (excepting
S. inermis
). Apparently, larger males display positive allometry in the shape of the prothorax, i.e., the pronotum is distinctly expanded, the prothoracic leg is very long, and anteroventral margin of the protibia bears more and larger dentes ( Franz 1999 ).

